      <div id="aboutAuthor" class=" clearFloats bigBox"><div class="h2Container gradientHeaderContainer"><h2 class="brownBackground"><a href="/author/show/15445.Carl_Bernstein">About Carl Bernstein</a></h2></div><div class="bigBoxBody"><div class="bigBoxContent containerWithHeaderContent">
          <div class='bookAuthorProfile'>
<div class='bookAuthorProfile__topContainer'>
<div class='bookAuthorProfile__photoContainer'>
<a href="/author/show/15445.Carl_Bernstein"><div class='bookAuthorProfile__photo' style='background-image: url(https://images.gr-assets.com/authors/1214425238p3/15445.jpg);'></div>
</a></div>
<div class='bookAuthorProfile__widgetContainer'>
<div class='bookAuthorProfile__name'>
<a href="/author/show/15445.Carl_Bernstein">Carl Bernstein
</a></div>
<div class='bookAuthorProfile__followerCount'>
380
followers
</div>

</div>
</div>
<div class='bookAuthorProfile__about'>

<span id="freeTextContainer10971437672421180125">Carl Bernstein is an American journalist who, as a reporter for <i>The Washington Post</i> along with Bob Woodward, broke the story of the Watergate break-in and consequently helped bring about the resignation of United States President Richard Nixon. For his role in breaking the scandal, Bernstein received many awards; his work helped earn the Post a Pulitzer Prize for Public Service in 1973.</span>

</div>
</div>

